OL,6,FJames Wallace, the chief executive of
OL,7,Fcampaign group River Action, said:
OL,8,F"We're being told to celebrate the
OL,9,F'record investment' of water
OL,10,Fcompanies, but in reality, it is the
OL,11,Fpublic that will pay the price for
OL,12,Ftheir decades of neglect.
OL,14,F"Instead of fixing crumbling
OL,15,Finfrastructure, water companies have
OL,16,Fsaddled themselves with billions in
OL,17,Fjunk debt, leaving us with sewage-
OL,18,Fchoked rivers, and paying extortionate
OL,19,Finterest rates through bill hikes.
